# Copy this file to `.env` or `.env.local` in the repository / package root (the directory
# that contains the `server/` app folder) and set the value. Both names are gitignored;
# `.env.local` overrides `.env` for duplicate keys.
#
# PACHINKO_SESSION_JWT_SECRET — used only to sign the httpOnly session cookie (JWT). It is
# not a user password, not an API key, and is not stored in the database.
#
# Generate a new value (pick one, then paste the single line of output as the value):
#   openssl rand -base64 48
#   node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(48).toString('base64'))"
#
# In Docker, Kubernetes, or other hosts, set the same variable in the environment or
# secret store instead of a file. When running a published build, the working directory
# is often the same root where this file lives, so a root `.env` is picked up as intended.
PACHINKO_SESSION_JWT_SECRET=
